<br>
I would rather that this thread was about the effect. That is, which consequenses is the structure &amp; levels of PoP having for playability.<br>
<br>
To put it short: many people I used to play with are &quot;taking a break from EQ&quot;, myself included. This started slowly about 2 months ago, and has escalated somewhat. The major reason for this I hear that people suddenly grew bored of the game. Which I find strange, because if people continually find fun stuff to do for 2-4 years, it doesn't suddenly go away, I should mean.<br>
<br>
The boring part is of course that most people I know are reduced to play (effectively) in 2 zones: PoS &amp; PoV. We are generally not keyed for the higher zones in PoP, although many of us carry around medallions, giant heads, etc, and therefore potentially could obtain PoP keys in the future. But people cannot be bothered to do so, I am afraid. <br>
<br>
EQ is now WAY to small a world for 62+, with 100+ relative &quot;noob zones&quot;, and 2 playable zones for people like me. Other computer game are beginning to offer competitive gameplay, I would say. PoP was the best thing that happened to EQ's game engine, but at the same time the biggest reduction in the virtual world. Trial of Justice was VERY entertaining, but the other key quests are not.<br>
<br>
I don't think the people I know will leave the game over this at this point. More likely they will put their character on hold, untill a 61+ expansion arrives, with some rare gamesession from time to time, while waiting.<br>
<br>
Is this a local phenomena around me, or is it general?<br>
 <p>Iblis<br>
Archmage of the Heralds of Dawn<br>
