<br>
More and more, I find myself doing things that gain me zero experience, just so I can do stuff other than exp grind in the same spots.  I try and have fun, but it's sort of hard to not notice the lack of experience gain.  Hopefully playing a twinked low level frog will be fun.<br>
<br>
I haven't actually noticed a large number of people retiring from EQ over this, however.  I imagine people in uber guilds are not as bothered, since they have so much stuff to raid, and PoP has only been out a few months, so people who don't get bored easily/don't play much are not burnt out on the few high lvl exp zones yet.  I would guess that this becomes more of a problem over the next half year or so, unless SoE quickly cranks out another &quot;extension&quot; for non-raid fiend lvl 61+ folks in the near future. <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=azzabarr@themagicianstower>Azzabarr</A> at: 1/27/03 1:52:07 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=ailees>Ailees</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ikebana-toulouse.com/maitres/ailees.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Sage</span><br>  Posts: 838<br> <font color=#333333>(1/27/03 2:15:58 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm46.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=185.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.ikebana-toulouse.com/citation/ailee3.jpg WIDTH=138 HEIGHT=190></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: PoP - Levels II.</span><hr size=1> This is not exact.<br>
