<br>
-- Reduced the level range of mobs for hunting<br>
-- Added a huge experience modifier on PoP zones without touching the rest of the game<br>
-- Pre-pop added a bonus for killing mobs closer to your level, which was ok while there were plenty of level 55 mobs in the Luclin era, but problematic when you moved over 60 and were limited to PoP for this bonus.<br>
<br>
These three changes were really done for the sub-60 crowd.  It moved the level 60's who were &quot;slumming&quot; in Seb and Velk out for more appropriate level characters to move in.  Not that they took advantage of it, because with PoP experience in tier 1, most of them got level 60 in a few weeks of casual play.  PoP made levels 50-60 and easy as Kunark made 40-50.<br>
<br>
But then came the real clincher:<br>
<br>
-- Put bottlenecks on moving to higher zones.  Whether these bottlenecks are difficult in one person's mind or easy to another makes no difference - They are bottlenecks.<br>
<br>
The end result was obvious to see shortly after PoP came out:  Far too many players crowded into a few zones.<br>
<br>
Even if you do you the quests for tier 3, you are unlikely to get a group in most of these bring-your-own-group zones.  The guilds that did the events for flags have enough people in there to form their own groups most of the time.  Only members of the &quot;needed&quot; classes (slowers, clerics, and tanks) have much of a chance at getting an invite.<br>
<br>
The decision to make LoY an expansion for levels 35-60 boggles my mind.  PoP already opened up so many zones that were previously closed to these levels by moving the 60+ folks out of them.  And these zones are highly underutilized at this point.  Just bump up the exp modifiers on Seb, Velk, Chardok and some others to PoP levels and you'll find the 50-58 crowd moving back there.  They really didn't need need to build *new* zones for those levels - They are needed for the 60+.<br>
<br>
My prediction?  LoY zones will be the least used of any expansion so far.  Previously that title went to Velious, but it was primarily built as a raid expansion.  LoY is being built for experience, and it misses the mark entirely. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=skidogg>SkiDogg</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 43<br> <font color=#333333>(1/31/03 8:26:48 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm46.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=185.topic&index=15>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: comment</span><hr size=1> No reason not to lvl to 65 for if your only worried about xp.  At 65 i can get 5 -6 aa's in a normal day easy.  But if your worried bout lack of content your right, it sucks like no tomarrow.  I play once or twice a week now.  Have the main aa's i want and no reason to waste my time xping.  Please god make LoY fun enough to make my 12 bucks a month worth it again.  <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=215051">Arch Convoker <br>
